# DWT stands for Discrete Wavelet Transform. This script contains functions that
# use the DWT to denoise a signal. This is accomplished by 3 steps:
#     1) Deconstruct the signal into frequency domain coefficiantes
#     2) Threshold these coefficients
#     3) Reconstruct with thresholded coefficients
#
# The threshold is a fixed form value proportional to log(length(signal)), which
# yields minimax performance; minimax performance is the minimum, over a given
# set of functions, of the maximum mean square error.
#
# Soft thresholding is used on the coefficients:
#     eta(x) = 0, if x < threshold;
#            = (x - threshold), else.
